post_text:
As part of the Re-Opening Plan for the 2020-2021 School Year, students will be required to use their district issued devices for Live Online Learning. The district has partnered with T-Mobile for a limited supply of mobile hotspots for households that do not have access to reliable Internet service. These hotspots will provide filtered Internet access only using student accounts and only on district devices. In order to identify which households, need these hotspots, we ask that you fill out a brief survey on the district website. Please do not complete the survey if you currently have adequate high-speed Internet. To ensure we are prepared to meet your children’s needs for the start of the school year, please complete this survey by Friday, August 14th. The School District would like to thank you for your cooperation during these unique times.

https://www.reynolds.k12.pa.us/

post_text: Congratulations to junior Finn Morgan, who was selected through virtual audition to this year's PMEA All-State Concert Band. Finn was the top-ranked euphonium player in PMEA Region 1, which is a 9-county area including the Pittsburgh metro area. Although the All-State festival was cancelled due to the current pandemic, this gave Finn the right to submit an audition to be accepted into the National Association for Music Education's Eastern Division Concert Band, which is comprised of students from 11 states; Washington, D.C., and Europe. He will be informed of audition results in the fall.

This is a reminder by order of the Governor of Pennsylvania, all Pennsylvania schools are closed for the remainder of the school year. Remote Learning will continue to follow the remaining approved school calendar. All events at Reynolds School District have been cancelled, this includes the Prom and Commencement. Our staff is working hard to create a video Commencement Ceremony to celebrate our wonderful senior class that will be available on the school district website on May 29, 2020.

Additionally, the district will be delivering classroom materials as well as Senior caps and gowns for any student who was unable to pick-up materials last week. These materials will be delivered tomorrow, Tuesday, April 28, 2020.

post_text: Finn Morgan (grade 11, euphonium), Rebekah Gaber (grade 11, oboe), and Brooklynn Mariacher (grade 11, contra alto clarinet), participated in the PMEA District 5 Band Festival held February 13-15, 2020 at Butler Intermediate High School. Finn earned 1st chair in the euphonium section and served as the euphonium soloist for the concert. He also qualified to move on to the PMEA Region 1 Band Festival, which will be held at Moon Area High School March 26-28, 2020. Additionally, Rebekah and Brooklynn each qualified as 1st alternates to the Region 1 Band Festival in their respective sections.

shared_text:
Reynolds Wrestling Mag
December 19, 2019 at 10:11 PM ·

BIG NEWS ALERT

GARY STEEN IS 44TH RAIDER TO REACH 100 WINS

Raider Gary Steen celebrates career win No. 100 Thursday night with his pal Griffin Taylor.

Gary, a junior, wasted little time in reaching the milestone win as he secured a first-period fall.

"Gary's teammates and coaches are extremely proud of him for joining the 100-Win Club, especially so early in his career," said Coach Casey Taylor.

"The best part, in my eyes, is that he is not satisfied. He continues to set his goals high and work very hard to reach them."

Gary becomes the 44th Reynolds High School wrestler to reach the century mark in victories.

The Raider Cross Country team represented RHS with a great showing at the state cross country meet Saturday.
Troy Hart placed 12th in the boys varsity race while Hannah Wagner placed 11th in the girls varsity race. Bethany Litwiler placed 66th in the girls race.
Both Troy and Hannah brought back metals in a field of over 200 runners.
Congratulations to all of you on a job well done.

post_text:
Due to inclement weather we have regretfully decided to cancel tonight’s Homecoming Parade and Bonfire. The event will not be rescheduled due to conflicting schedules and a restricted timeline on Friday. Parade floats will be on display for all to see during Friday Night’s Homecoming Football game.
We apologize for the cancellation of this great event. Our staff and students have committed a great deal of time in preparation and we do not want to run the risk of their floats being ruined by the conflicting weather reports of rain.
